Erl4j provides a framework for creating Java daemons that can respond to Erlang RPC messages. 

Dependencies:
 * jsvc 1.0.1 (http://commons.apache.org/daemon/jsvc.html)
 * Jinterface 1.5.1 (part of Erlang/OTP)
 * Rake 0.8.7
 
Erl4j may work with other versions of those dependencies, but those are just the ones I've tested it in.

To use Erl4j, you just have to implement the Erl4jHandler interface and update bin/erl4jctl.conf to use your Erl4jHandler implementation class. 

See erl4j-sample/com/syntacticbayleaves/erl4j/SampleErl4jDispatcher.java and erl4j-sample/com/syntacticbayleaves/erl4j/SampleErl4jHandler.java for examples.

To start a server with the samples, run:
  rake run


